      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import tensorflow as tf\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "E2ld8Iet167W"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "N = 64              # Number of subcarriers\n",
        "num_samples = 10000\n",
        "snr_db = 10\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "GAMreIeu2Byr"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Map bit pairs to QPSK symbols\n",
        "def qpsk_mod(bits):\n",
        "    bits = bits.reshape((-1, 2))\n",
        "    mapping = {\n",
        "        (0,0): 1+1j,\n",
        "        (0,1): 1-1j,\n",
        "        (1,0): -1+1j,\n",
        "        (1,1): -1-1j\n",
        "    }\n",
        "    return np.array([mapping[tuple(b)] for b in bits])\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "dBFVqJee2Miu"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Add AWGN noise to signal based on given SNR\n",
        "def awgn(signal, snr_db):\n",
        "    snr = 10**(snr_db/10)\n",
        "    power = np.mean(np.abs(signal)**2)\n",
        "    noise_power = power/snr\n",
        "    noise = np.sqrt(noise_power/2) * (\n",
        "        np.random.randn(*signal.shape) +\n",
        "        1j*np.random.randn(*signal.shape)\n",
        "    )\n",
        "    return signal + noise\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Fr9hPnsB2OxE"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Generate training dataset (per-subcarrier features and labels)\n",
        "X = []\n",
        "Y = []\n",
        "\n",
        "for _ in range(num_samples):\n",
        "\n",
        "    bits = np.random.randint(0,2,2*N)\n",
        "    tx_symbols = qpsk_mod(bits)\n",
        "\n",
        "    ofdm_time = np.fft.ifft(tx_symbols)\n",
        "    rx_time = awgn(ofdm_time, snr_db)\n",
        "    rx_symbols = np.fft.fft(rx_time)\n",
        "\n",
        "    for i in range(N):\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Input = single received symbol (real, imag)\n",
        "        X.append([rx_symbols[i].real, rx_symbols[i].imag])\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Label = corresponding transmitted symbol\n",
        "        s = tx_symbols[i]\n",
        "\n",
        "        if s == 1+1j: Y.append(0)\n",
        "        elif s == 1-1j: Y.append(1)\n",
        "        elif s == -1+1j: Y.append(2)\n",
        "        else: Y.append(3)\n",
        "\n",
        "X = np.array(X)\n",
        "Y = np.array(Y)\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Unz3mn1k2SPq"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "model = Sequential([\n",
        "    Dense(32, activation='relu', input_shape=(2,)),\n",
        "    Dense(32, activation='relu'),\n",
        "    Dense(4, activation='softmax')\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "model.compile(\n",
        "    optimizer='adam',\n",
        "    loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',\n",
        "    metrics=['accuracy']\n",
        ")\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6wjyahaL2Yb0",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "outputId": "d80a3042-1c33-4abf-9d8a-d09e46510882"
      },

        "# Predict class for a single test sample\n",

      "source": [
        "def classical_detector(rx_symbols):\n",
        "\n",
        "    detected = []\n",
        "\n",
        "    for s in rx_symbols:\n",
        "\n",
        "        real = 1 if s.real > 0 else -1\n",
        "        imag = 1 if s.imag > 0 else -1\n",
        "\n",
        "        if real==1 and imag==1:\n",
        "            detected.append(0)\n",
        "        elif real==1 and imag==-1:\n",
        "            detected.append(1)\n",
        "        elif real==-1 and imag==1:\n",
        "            detected.append(2)\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            detected.append(3)\n",
        "\n",
        "    return np.array(detected)\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {

      },

        "\n",
        "        for i in range(N):\n",
        "\n",
        "            # Per-subcarrier input for DL\n",
        "            X_test.append([rx_symbols[i].real, rx_symbols[i].imag])\n",
        "\n",
        "            # Label\n",
        "            s = tx_symbols[i]\n",
        "            if s == 1+1j: Y_test.append(0)\n",

        "            else: Y_test.append(3)\n",

        "    Y_test = np.array(Y_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # ---------- DL Detection ----------\n",

        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense\n"

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# System Parameters\n",
        "num_bits = 20000\n",
        "snr_range = np.arange(0, 21, 5)   # 0 to 20 dB\n",
        "\n",
        "ber_classical_adv = []\n",

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def qpsk_mod(bits):\n",
        "    bits_reshaped = bits.reshape(-1, 2)\n",
        "    symbols = 2*bits_reshaped - 1\n",
        "    return symbols[:,0] + 1j*symbols[:,1]\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "kosDgZObh2C2"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def classical_detector(symbols):\n",
        "    detected_bits = []\n",
        "\n",
        "    for sym in symbols:\n",
        "        bit1 = 1 if np.real(sym) > 0 else 0\n",
        "        bit2 = 1 if np.imag(sym) > 0 else 0\n",
        "        detected_bits.extend([bit1, bit2])\n",
        "\n",
        "    return np.array(detected_bits)\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "1is0hbPNh7ft"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "model = Sequential([\n",
        "    Dense(32, activation='relu', input_shape=(2,)),\n",
        "    Dense(32, activation='relu'),\n",
        "    Dense(2, activation='sigmoid')\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "model.compile(optimizer='adam',\n",
        "              loss='binary_crossentropy',\n",
        "              metrics=['accuracy'])\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"

            "  super().__init__(activity_regularizer=activity_regularizer, **kwargs)\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Training Data\n",
        "train_bits = np.random.randint(0, 2, num_bits)\n",
        "train_symbols = qpsk_mod(train_bits)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Rayleigh Fading Channel\n",
        "h_train = (np.random.randn(len(train_symbols)) +\n",
        "           1j*np.random.randn(len(train_symbols))) / np.sqrt(2)\n",
        "\n",
        "faded_train = h_train * train_symbols\n",
        "\n",
        "# AWGN Noise\n",
        "snr_train_db = 10\n",
        "snr_linear = 10**(snr_train_db/10)\n",
        "noise_var = 1/snr_linear\n",
        "\n",
        "noise = np.sqrt(noise_var/2) * (\n",
        "        np.random.randn(len(train_symbols)) +\n",
        "        1j*np.random.randn(len(train_symbols)))\n",
        "\n",
        "rx_train = faded_train + noise\n",
        "\n",
        "# Equalization\n",
        "rx_equalized = rx_train / h_train\n",
        "\n",
        "# DL Features\n",
        "X_train = np.column_stack((np.real(rx_equalized),\n",
        "                           np.imag(rx_equalized)))\n",
        "\n",
        "y_train = train_bits.reshape(-1,2)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Train Model\n",
        "model.fit(X_train, y_train,\n",
        "          epochs=10,\n",
        "          batch_size=256,\n",
        "          verbose=1)\n"
      ],

        "for snr_db in snr_range:\n",
        "\n",
        "    bits = np.random.randint(0, 2, num_bits)\n",
        "    symbols = qpsk_mod(bits)\n",
        "\n",

        "\n",
        "The experiment demonstrates that Deep Neural Network (DNN) detectors consistently outperform classical methods in OFDM symbol detection, particularly in challenging Rayleigh fading channels.
